SIMPLE: sinuate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinuate
<hw>Sin"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sinuatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>sinuare</ets> to wind, bend, fr.
<ets>sinus</ets> a bend.]</ety> <def>Having the margin alternately
curved inward and outward; having rounded lobes separated by rounded
sinuses; sinuous; wavy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinuate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sinuate
<hw>Sin"u*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sinuated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Sinuating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To bend or curve in
and out; to wind; to turn; to be sinuous.</def>
<rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinuated</ent>⟦br⟧
